kpi_info.title: HS_SCCH_PWR_DIST_CLASS_0
kpi_info.use: The HS-SCCH transmit power measurement. Number of TTIs matching to power limit of class 0 (default range; lower than 0.1 W). UPDATED:The HS-SCCH transmit power is measured by each active TTI (when sending data) in BTS. The each active TTI increments the correct class of the HS-SCCH power distribution. I.e. the number of TTIs (2 ms) in different class indicates the amount of time spent

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_HSFACH_RX
kpi_info.use: Duration of UE in HSFACH RX (Reception) state. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the UE state is changing to the DRX state.

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_HSFACH_DRX
kpi_info.use: Duration of UE in HSFACH DRX (Discontinuous Reception) state. UPDATED: This counter is updated when the UE state is changing to the RX state.

kpi_info.title: EFACH_UE_SUM
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled number of users in Enhanced Cell FACH state. UPDATED: Every 100ms the number of users in Enhanced CELL_FACH is sampled and summed to this counter.

kpi_info.title: MAX_EFACH_USERS
kpi_info.use: Max value for concurrent users in Enhanced Cell FACH state. UPDATED: The counter is updated over the measurement period. The value of the counter is the maximum value of all samples for the number of users in Enhanced CELL_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: DND_CEDCH_RSRC
kpi_info.use: The number of PRACH Preambles received by BTS that were not granted a Common E-DCH Resource. UPDATED: The counter is updated when the PRACH Preamble was not granted and the BTS DSP report for Common E-DCH resource usage contains "Denied E-DCH Resources" indicator.

kpi_info.title: ACTIVE_DC_MIMO_USERS_2C_SUM
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of active DC-HSDPA MIMO users. Active DC-HSDPA MIMO users use both carriers for transmission. This counter, divided by the denominator M5000C327, provides the average number of active DC-HSDPA MIMO users with two carriers. When this counter is updated the counter M5000C328 is updated also. UPDATED: The number of DC-HSDPA MIMO users is sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter. Only users which use both carriers for transmission within one TTI are counted. The counter is updated for both (primary and secondary) cells.

kpi_info.title: ACTIVE_DC_MIMO_USERS_1C_SUM
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of active DC-HSDPA MIMO users. Active DC-HSDPA MIMO users use only one carrier for transmission. This counter, divided by the denominator M5000C327, provides the average number of active DC-HSDPA MIMO users with one carrier. When this counter is updated the counter M5000C329 is updated also. UPDATED: The number of DC-HSDPA MIMO users is sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter. Only users which use only one carrier for transmission are counted. The counter is updated only if users receive data in measured cell.

kpi_info.title: CAPABLE_DC_MIMO_USERS_SUM
kpi_info.use: The sum of sampled values for the number of capable DC-HSDPA MIMO users. When this counter is updated the counter M5000C330 is updated also. UPDATED: The number of DC-HSDPA MIMO capable users is sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter. The counter is updated regardless of the fact whether users receive data or not.

kpi_info.title: TTI_DCMIMO_HSDPA_USER_PC_1C_D
kpi_info.use: Scheduled DC-HSDPA + MIMO users only from primary carrier when one carrier and MIMO Dual Stream is used. When this counter is updated the counters M5000C331 and M5000C336 are updated also. UPDATED: The counter is updated by 1 if TTI was scheduled from primary carrier to DC+MIMO user when only one carrier and Dual Stream was used.

kpi_info.title: TTI_DCMIMO_HSDPA_USER_PC_1C_S
kpi_info.use: Scheduled DC-HSDPA + MIMO users only from primary carrier when one carrier and MIMO Single Stream is used. UPDATED: The counter is updated by 1 if TTI was scheduled from primary carrier to DC+MIMO user when only one carrier and Single Stream was used.

kpi_info.title: TTI_DCMIMO_HSDPA_USER_SC_1C_D
